author: Jackie Willis
title: Chrissy Teigen Compares John Legend to Arthur Cartoon in Funny Tweet
text: Chrissy Teigen Compares John Legend to Arthur Cartoon in Funny Tweet by Jackie Willis 6:21 AM PST, February 22, 2017 Photo: Getty Images The Internet has found John Legend's animated doppelganger. After his role in La La Land where he sports a yellow turtleneck, the Internet started noticing that the 38-year-old R&B singer resembled the Arthur cartoon character, who also wears a yellow sweater. Even Legend's wife, Chrissy Teigen, got in on the fun, tweeting a photo of the animated aardvark clinching his fist. "John when you tell him he looks like Arthur," she quipped. John Legend look like Arthur lowkey pic.twitter.com/bfeG3cYo4M Legend responded to his wife's message, writing: "I hadn't even heard of this Arthur character 'til now. Was he around when I was a kid?" John when you tell him he looks like Arthur pic.twitter.com/0NW3NDtAb1 — christine teigen (@chrissyteigen) February 21, 2017 @chrissyteigen I hadn't even heard of this Arthur character til now. Was he around when I was a kid? — John Legend (@johnlegend) February 21, 2017 To be fair, the cartoon didn't air until 1996. WATCH: Chrissy Teigen Asks John Legend If He's Mad at Her for Getting Drunk at GRAMMYs in Series of Funny Snaps The couple will surely have more silly tweets when Teigen and their daughter, Luna, join Legend on tour. "Oh my God, I much prefer life on the road. I like moving a lot. I like cooking on the bus. I like the bus life," the 31-year-old model raved to ET while at the GRAMMYs earlier this month. "It's like video games on the bus all the time. All day, I tweet." RELATED SLIDESHOW
